<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.893720>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Adult female of Coccus praetermissus Lin & Tanaka, sp. n. ANT: antenna; AP: anal plate; DA: dorsal areolations; DMD: dorsal microduct; DS: dorsal seta; DT: dorsal tubercle; DTD: dorsal tubular duct; LG: leg; MP: multilocular pore; MS: marginal setae; PAP: preantennal pore; POP: preopercular pores; SP: spiracular pore; SSP: stigmatic spines; VMD: ventral microduct; VTD: ventral tubular duct. Scale bars: 200 µm for ANT, AP; 100 µm for DA, LG; 50 µm for SSP; 10 µm for other details." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/893720/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

